  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2003-05-01",
    "date": "2006-11-28T17:35:40Z",
    "text": "Requires the Director of the Office of Domestic Preparedness of the Department of Homeland Security to allow any State to request approval to reallocate funds received pursuant to the State Homeland Security Grant Program among the four specified categories of equipment, training, exercises, and planning. Requires the Director to approve such requests in accordance with the State plan and any other relevant factors as determined by the Secretary of Homeland Security."
